  <h4><a name="h.7chc2jyk8tyu" id="h.7chc2jyk8tyu"></a>How to get to
  the trailhead</h4>

  <p>The Milford Track is located in Fiordland National Park. Walking
  the Milford Track requires bus or private transport to Te Anau Downs, then a boat trip
  (1 hour 15 min) to Glade Wharf, the start of the track. Boat transport  (15 min)
  is also required from Sandfly Point, at the end of the track, to Milford
  Sound/Piopiotahi.</p>

  

  <p>Travelling by road: between Te Anau and Te Anau Downs (27 km),
  between Milford Sound and Te Anau (120 km) and between Te Anau and Queenstown (197
  km)</p>

  

  <p>During the Great Walks season (late October to late April) there
  are regular transport services to and from the Milford Track.</p>

  

